Netherlands Nips Brazil in World Cup Volleyball 
The Netherlands scored a surprise victory over Olympic title holder
Brazil in four sets at the World Cup Men's Volleyball Tournament in
Kagoshima on Wednesday.
The Dutch spikers held off its South American opponents in a hard
fought battle with 17-15, 12-15, 15-7 and 17-16.
The Netherlands, runners-up of the 1994 Barcelona Olympic games and the
world championships, joined Brazil and Cuba to have a win and loss
record of 3-1 with the victory.
The unbeaten Italian team beat the Chinese squad 15-4, 15-3, 15-3 in a
Hiroshima match to stretch its winning streak to four to take the lead.
In other earlier two matches in the two cities, Cuba downed African
champions Tunisia 15-5, 6-15, 15-5, 15-6 while Argentina blanked Canada
15-8, 15-8, 15-8.
